<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="99" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,434,1899]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1730,1755]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[328,557,1730,1755]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Piruanycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wappesi">
<emphasis box="[328,557,1730,1755]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Piruanycha wappesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other species of the genus by antennomere III with long setae throughout (only on ventral side in the other species), and by the tarsomeres proportionally smaller and narrower (
<figureCitation box="[159,241,1802,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 45. 37 – 39" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1892,1914]" captionTargetBox="[245,1363,203,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[218,1375,195,1847]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 45. 37 – 39. Lamacoscylus albatus, holotype female: 37. Dorsal habitus; 38. Ventral habitus; 39. Lateral habitus. 40 – 43. Lamacoscylus obscurus, holotype male: 40. Dorsal habitus; 41. Ventral habitus; 42. Lateral habitus; 43. Head, frontal view. 44. Piruanycha pitilla Galileo &amp; Martins, 2005, holotype female, protarsus, dorsal view. 45. Piruanycha wappesi, holotype female, protarsus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236729/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,241,1802,1827]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
) (larger and wider in the other species (
<figureCitation box="[686,769,1802,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 45. 37 – 39" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1892,1914]" captionTargetBox="[245,1363,203,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[218,1375,195,1847]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 45. 37 – 39. Lamacoscylus albatus, holotype female: 37. Dorsal habitus; 38. Ventral habitus; 39. Lateral habitus. 40 – 43. Lamacoscylus obscurus, holotype male: 40. Dorsal habitus; 41. Ventral habitus; 42. Lateral habitus; 43. Head, frontal view. 44. Piruanycha pitilla Galileo &amp; Martins, 2005, holotype female, protarsus, dorsal view. 45. Piruanycha wappesi, holotype female, protarsus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/236729/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">
Fig. 
<number box="[738,769,1803,1827]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99" value="44.0">44</number>
</figureCitation>
)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="99" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,434,1899]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1838,1863]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species is named for James E. Wappes (
<collectionCode box="[859,946,1839,1863]" pageId="18" pageNumber="99">ACMT</collectionCode>
), for his friendship and constant help with providing specimens for study.
</paragraph>
